<!-- §9 What is a 3D moon lamp -->
<h2 style="font-size: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 1rem;">What is a 3D Printed Moon Lamp?</h2>
<p style="color: var(--foreground); line-height: 1.6; margin-bottom: 1rem;">A 3D printed moon lamp is a decorative light fixture designed to replicate the lunar surface in miniature. Using PLA plastic (a biodegradable polymer), manufacturers create a sphere with detailed, photorealistic crater texture that mimics actual moon topography. Inside, an LED provides warm ambient light that diffuses through the plastic, creating a soft glow.</p>
<p style="color: var(--foreground); line-height: 1.6; margin-bottom: 1rem;">The 3D Printed Moon Lamp – Jupiter Night Light comes in multiple sizes (8–20cm) and two control types: simple 2-color manual (warm white and warm yellow) toggled by a button, or feature-rich 16-color remote version with adjustable brightness, timer modes, and color memory. All variants are USB-powered and built to last 10,000+ hours—roughly 3+ years of 8-hour nightly use.</p>
<p style="color: var(--foreground); line-height: 1.6;">Unlike projectors or light strips, the moon lamp is a static, sculptural accent piece. You're buying both functional lighting and artwork. It works on nightstands, shelves, desks, and as a standalone floor lamp. The realistic surface texture is the star—sunlight will reveal all the lunar detail, and LED glow at night turns it into a glowing moon floating in your room.</p>

